****************************************************************************************************
************************************** Work Flow ***************************************************
**************************************************************************************************** 
To be used in producer / consumer pattern combined with repository pattern
.NET Core MVC + Entity Framework Core + SQL Server (Docker) 

1. The user is met with a login window. They then authenticate into SQL server

2. Once logged in you can select an existing camera or discover a new camera
    If viewing existing camera, there are 2 features: playback and analytics.
    If discovering new camera, select subnet, ping subnet and apply ONVIF protocol (for now)
    Add the results to table view.
    


















Modules needed:

The Data Plane:
Camera: onvif/ discovery
        rtsp steam (main and substream)
        possible events?
        FFMPEG??
        RTSP camera →  MediaMTX WebRTC gateway → Browser
        
        receive -> relay to another browser -> record
              
        
Stream:
          connect to cameras - stay stable
          handles auth per camera + permissions
          pull rtsp and server to clients      
        
        
The Control Plane:
Recorder:
        incoming stream and write video to disk
        create timeline/index
        manage retention        

Api Server(Controller):
        the brains
        store meta data, users, camera configs
        rest endpoints for ui + admin actions
Client
        live view
        talks to Api server for permissions
        
  
